      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:4:3:8:6",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " سُلَيْمَانَ بْنَ دَاوُدَ حَجَّ الْبَيْتَ فِي الْجِنِّ وَ الْإِنْسِ وَ الطَّيْرِ وَ الرِّيَاحِ وَ كَسَا الْبَيْتَ الْقَبَاطِيَّ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Fazzal, from Ali Bin Uqba, from his father, from Zurara, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> that Suleyman<sup>as</sup> Bin Dawood<sup>as</sup> performed Hajj of the House (Kaaba) among the Jinn and the humans, and the birds, and the winds, and a cloak of the household tapestries’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "6. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn Faddal from Ali ibn ‘Uqbah, from his father from Zurarah who has said the following: “Abu Ja’far, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Sulayman son of Dawud (Solomon son of David) performed Hajj along with Jinn, man, bird and wind, wearing a Coptic gown.’” "
        ]
      }
    }
